# Phase A-1: logo partition write verify test
# Executed: 2026-07-01T19:18:11+09:00

## Objective
Determine whether Sunmi LK verifies logo partition (mmcblk0p28, 8MB).

## Method
- Copy dump/logo.img
- Modify last byte: 0x00 -> 0xFF (safe zone, trailing zeros)
- Flash to /dev/block/platform/bootdevice/by-name/logo via mtk-su + dd
- Verify write with re-dump SHA256
- Reboot, measure time to boot_completed=1

## Results
- Original logo.img SHA256: b110cbdbd4bd4e4879e7e68898fc3bbb4398911bcda50c45c74a14a2e24c6e87
- Modified logo SHA256:     d3736b1bef448bce3e1a631b716a4f954ce0385615ffc66c5c5898680af67921
- After-write SHA256:        d3736b1bef448bce3e1a631b716a4f954ce0385615ffc66c5c5898680af67921 (match)
- Write dd: 8388608 bytes in 1.613s
- boot_completed=1 after 51s reboot
- adb device online, standard fingerprint
- Sunmi LK did NOT reject modified logo

## Conclusion
Sunmi LK does NOT verify logo partition. Non-critical / cosmetic partitions can be written freely.

## Next
Proceed to Phase A-2 (system 1-byte modification).
